The Belgian striker, Romelu Lukaku, arrived Italy on Wednesday on his return to Inter Milan after an unproductive season at Chelsea in England.  Lukaku arriving the city of Milan on Wednesday declared that said he is “very happy” to return to return to Inter Milan from Chelsea on loan.
Lukaku arrived the Linate airport, Milan, in the early hours of Wednesday.
The Belgian striker, 29 years, is expected to undergo medical test later in the day before proceeding on the formal return to Inter Milan.
